<h1 id="heading1">About GameForge</h1>

<div id="aboutus-card">

<!-- OUR HISTORY -->
<h3 style="color:#66c0f4;">🎮 Our History</h3>

<p style="color:#c7d5e0; font-size:14px; line-height:1.6;">
GameForge has been operating since <b>1985</b>. For decades the store has been a trusted
destination for gamers looking for the latest PC video games and accessories.
Originally, the store focused entirely on <b>physical media</b> such as CDs, floppy disks,
and other game formats that were popular during the early years of PC gaming.
</p>

<p style="color:#c7d5e0; font-size:14px; line-height:1.6;">
As the gaming industry evolved and digital media became more common,
the owners of GameForge decided that the business needed to modernize
in order to keep up with the gaming industry.
</p>

<br>

<!-- PHYSICAL STORE -->
<h3 style="color:#66c0f4;">🏬 The Physical Store</h3>

<p style="color:#c7d5e0; font-size:14px; line-height:1.6;">
GameForge currently operates from its main store located in <b>Price Plaza</b>.
Inside the store, games are organized on shelves in plain view and sorted
into categories so customers can easily browse for the types of games they enjoy.
</p>

<ul style="color:#c7d5e0; text-align:left; font-size:14px; line-height:1.6;">
<li>A section dedicated to <b>used games</b>.</li>
<li>Lists of popular <b>video game franchises</b>.</li>
<li>A <b>demo station</b> where customers can try games before purchasing.</li>
<li>A front desk staffed by employees who assist customers and process purchases.</li>
</ul>

<p style="color:#c7d5e0; font-size:14px; line-height:1.6;">
While the physical store has served gamers well for many years,
it has some limitations such as limited stock availability, theft,
and accidental damage to physical game copies.
</p>

<br>

<!-- GOING DIGITAL -->
<h3 style="color:#66c0f4;">🌐 Moving to a Digital Platform</h3>

<p style="color:#c7d5e0; font-size:14px; line-height:1.6;">
To overcome these limitations, GameForge is expanding into a
<b>digital gaming store</b>. This will allow gamers to purchase
and download games online without needing to visit the store.
</p>

<h4 style="color:#66c0f4;">Benefits of Going Online</h4>

<ul style="color:#c7d5e0; text-align:left; font-size:14px; line-height:1.6;">
<li><b>Global Accessibility</b> – Customers can access the store 24/7 from anywhere.</li>
<li><b>Scalability</b> – Digital games can be distributed without additional physical costs.</li>
<li><b>No Physical Clutter</b> – No discs, scratches, or storage issues.</li>
<li><b>Easier Updates</b> – Developers can release patches and updates instantly.</li>
<li><b>Direct to Consumer</b> – Publishers can release games directly on the platform.</li>
<li><b>Convenience</b> – Buy, download, and play instantly without visiting the store.</li>
</ul>

